Media Release: Update on the coronavirus by Premier Alan Winde 13 January 2021 eval(ez_write_tag([[468,60],'politicsweb_co_za-box-3','ezslot_9',112,'0','0']));As of 1pm on 13 January, the Western Cape has 39 491 active Covid-19 infections with a total of 245 343 confirmed Covid-19 cases and 197 224 recoveries. Total confirmed COVID-19 cases 245 343 Total recoveries 197 224 Total deaths 8628 Total active cases (currently infected patients) 39 491 Tests conducted 1129702 Hospitalisations 3528 with 384 of these in ICU or high care The Western Cape has recorded 146 additional deaths, bringing the total number of COVID-19 related deaths in the province to 8628. We send our condolences to their loved ones at this time. Additional data is available on the Western Cape Covid-19 data dashboard which also features active cases per sub-district, active cases per 100 000 and 7-day moving averages. Access the data dashboard here: https://coronavirus.westerncape.gov.za/covid-19-dashboard Issued by Office of Western Cape Premier, 13 January 2021 